snippet: The intrusion could have resulted in access of as many as 160,000 Social Security numbers, but officials think the actual number is far lower.
abstract: Officials say Washington State Administrative Office of the Courts was hacked sometime between fall 2012 and February 2013, and up to 160,000 Social Security numbers and one million driver's license numbers could have been obtained during data breach of its public Web site.
lead_paragraph: The intrusion could have resulted in access of as many as 160,000 Social Security numbers, but officials think the actual number is far lower.

headline.seo: Hackers Access Personal Data in Washington State
headline.main: Hackers Retrieve Personal Data in Washington State
